  &lt;p id="yiA2Qo"&gt;SteelSeries has debuted its Rival 5 wired, right-handed gaming mouse that is available right &lt;a href="https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;amp;xs=1&amp;amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsteelseries.com%2Fgaming-mice%2Frival-5&amp;amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2021%2F5%2F11%2F22428555%2Fsteelseries-rival-5-wired-gaming-mouse-price-specs" rel="sponsored nofollow noopener" target="_blank"&gt;now for $59.99&lt;/a&gt;. From a distance, the Rival 5 looks similar to the modular Rival 600, but this is a simpler and slightly more ergonomically friendly mouse. The overall shape of the device seems to have a softer curve, making it fit a little more comfortably for palm or fingertip grip users. &lt;/p&gt;
